==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Intact
<hw>In*tact"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>intactus</ets>; pref. <ets>in-</ets> not + <ets>tactus</ets>, p. p.
of <ets>tangere</ets> to touch: cf. F. <ets>intact</ets>. See
<er>In-</er> not, and <er>Tact</er>, <er>Tangent</er>.]</ety>
<def>Untouched, especially by anything that harms, defiles, or the like;
uninjured; undefiled; left complete or entire.</def>
<rj><au>Buckle.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>When all external differences have passed away, one element
remains <qex>intact</qex>, unchanged, -- the everlasting basis of our
common nature, the human soul.</q> <rj><qau>F. W.
Robertson.</qau></rj></p>

<p><ent>Intactable</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Intactible</ent>⟦br⟧
